   <refnamediv>
 
       <refname>invpd</refname>
 
               <refpurpose>mimic Gauss function invpd </refpurpose>
 
   </refnamediv>
 
 
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
 
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
 
               <synopsis>[xi]=invpd(x)</synopsis>
 
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
 
 
        <refsection>
 
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
 
           <variablelist>
 
           <varlistentry>
 
 
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> x </term> =    a square matrix </para></listitem>
 
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
 
 
          <varlistentry>
 
 
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> xi </term> =    inverse of x </para></listitem>
 
 
 
          </varlistentry>
 
          </variablelist>
 
        </refsection>
 
 
 
        <refsection>
 
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
 
A dummy function to mimic Gauss invpd simply returns the inverse, with no checking for positive definiteness.
 
 
 
        </refsection>
 
 
 
        <refsection>
 
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
 
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
 
Y=invpd(x)
 
 
 
               ]]></programlisting>
 
        </refsection>
 
 
 
